	<item>
		<title>By: Kevin Werbach</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2005/07/tell-me-again-why-the-mac-is-better/#comment-32</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kevin Werbach]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 05 Jul 2005 17:41:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werbach.com/wordpress/?p=1239#comment-32</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I get the impression that Tiger (even 10.4.1, which I have) is still buggy and not yet really ready for prime time.  I&#039;m hoping that explains some of the problems I&#039;m having.  I haven&#039;t had another hard crash requring a restart, so maybe I&#039;ll find better stability than Windows after all.

I&#039;m loathe to call warranty service, which is bound to be a time suck, but I may be forced to if I can&#039;t get the USB drives working.  I use keychain drives all the time to transfer files.  Now that I&#039;ve moved all my files over, I also can&#039;t afford to give up the machine for any length of time.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I get the impression that Tiger (even 10.4.1, which I have) is still buggy and not yet really ready for prime time.  I&#8217;m hoping that explains some of the problems I&#8217;m having.  I haven&#8217;t had another hard crash requring a restart, so maybe I&#8217;ll find better stability than Windows after all.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m loathe to call warranty service, which is bound to be a time suck, but I may be forced to if I can&#8217;t get the USB drives working.  I use keychain drives all the time to transfer files.  Now that I&#8217;ve moved all my files over, I also can&#8217;t afford to give up the machine for any length of time.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
	</item>
